Qualifications: Fractionation was combined with mass spectrometry from five diverse animal species to predict co-complex protein interactions conserved across metazoa using an integrative computational scoring procedure along with an SVM approach. Qualifications: Within each experiment, reporter intensity values (protein peak areas) are normalized by calculating the median for each sample, equalizing the medians across all samples, and then subtracting the AP-MS results from the negative control (GFP-empty). The score represents the log2-transformed average of the adjusted binding intensity from three replicates.
